  Deleting your Deployment and Removing your Data 

IBM Cloud® Databases instances are softly deleted in production when you delete or deprovision the instance in IBM Cloud.

IBM Cloud keeps the deployment in the soft delete state for three days before it issues a delete. The soft delete state addresses use cases when you accidentally delete an instance. You can re-enable an existing soft-deleted instance on your own.

Because a soft delete is essentially a disablement, no IBM Cloud® Databases for DataStax deployment can recover from a soft delete. Once an IBM Cloud® Databases for DataStax deployment is deleted, that deployment must be restored from a backup.



  Deleting your Deployment in the User Interface 

To delete your deployment instance from the Resource list section dashboard of the IBM Cloud dashboard, select your deployment. Next, by using the stacked three-dot menu icon ( ![Stacked three dots icon](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs-content/v1/content/5561b38c6df9e8168523d143eaf64ab6acd7b600/cloud-databases/images/stacked-three-dots.png) ), choose Delete from the drop list.

