  Cryptoshredding keys 

Key Protect provides for a [force delete](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/key-protect?topic=key-protect-delete-keys) of a key that is in use by IBM Cloud® services, including your Cloud Databases deployments. This action is called cryptoshredding.

Cryptoshredding is a destructive action. When the key is deleted, your data is unrecoverable even from a soft delete state.





  Backups Removal 

